12/09/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski signed a decree Tuesday (September 11th) appointing Viktor Dimovski as head of the country's Intelligence Agency.
Predecessor Kire Naumov resigned for personal reasons.
Dimovski, a former ambassador to Belgrade and non-resident ambassador to Israel, previously served as deputy foreign minister responsible for Southeast European and Balkan affairs.
He also held senior posts at the interior ministry.
(Vecer, Dnevnik - 12/09/07;
MIA, A1 - 11/09/07)
